                <h1>MISSION</h1>
				The mission of your home materials shop should reflect your values, goals, and the unique services or products you offer. 
				It can include:

				<strong>Quality:</strong> Commitment to providing high-quality and durable home materials.
				<strong>Customer Satisfaction:</strong> A focus on delivering excellent service and ensuring customers 
				find what they need to create a comfortable home.
				<strong>Sustainability:</strong> If relevant, emphasize eco-friendly materials or responsible sourcing.
				<strong>Community Impact:</strong> Highlight how your shop supports local communities or contributes to local housing efforts.    
				<br><br>
				<h1>HISTORY</h1>
				If this is a new venture, your “history” will be your journey towards opening the shop.
				Consider documenting the steps and motivations behind starting the business. Key points might include:
				<br>
				<strong>Inception: </strong> Why did you decide to open a home materials shop?
				<br>
				(e.g., seeing a market need, passion for home improvement, or a family business legacy)
				<br><br>
				<strong>Growth Plan: </strong> What steps are you taking to build your business?<br>
				(e.g., product sourcing, finding a location, obtaining licenses)
				<br><br>
				<strong>Challenges Overcome:</strong>  Mention any hurdles you’ve faced or expect to face, and 
				how you plan to handle them.
